{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
    "name": "Rate Limiter API",
    "description": "Colección completa para probar el Rate Limiter NestJS.\n\nEndpoints organizados por categoría con tests automáticos que verifican:\n- Headers de rate limiting (X-RateLimit-Limit, X-RateLimit-Remaining, X-RateLimit-Reset)\n- Códigos de respuesta\n- Estructura del body\n\nCómo disparar el rate limit:\n- Usá el Postman Runner sobre la carpeta \"🔥 Stress Tests\"\n- Configura las iteraciones según el límite del endpoint",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:{{port}}",
      "type": "default"
    }
  ],
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [""]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Tests globales aplicados a TODOS los requests",
          "const rateLimitHeaders = ['X-RateLimit-Limit', 'X-RateLimit-Remaining', 'X-RateLimit-Reset'];",
          "",
          "if (pm.response.code !== 429) {",
          "  rateLimitHeaders.forEach(header => {",
          "    pm.test(`Header '${header}' presente`, () => {",
          "      pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get(header)).to.not.be.undefined;",
          "    });",
          "  });",
          "",
          "  // Guardar estado del rate limit en variables de entorno",
          "  const remaining = pm.response.headers.get('X-RateLimit-Remaining');",
          "  const limit = pm.response.headers.get('X-RateLimit-Limit');",
          "  if (remaining !== null) pm.environment.set('lastRemaining', remaining);",
          "  if (limit !== null) pm.environment.set('lastLimit', limit);",
          "}",
          "",
          "if (pm.response.code === 429) {",
          "  pm.test('429 tiene header Retry-After', () => {",
          "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Retry-After')).to.not.be.undefined;",
          "  });",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "🩺 Observability",
      "description": "Endpoints de salud y métricas del sistema. No tienen rate limit estricto.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["health"]
            },
            "description": "Verifica el estado del sistema incluyendo el storage backend.\n\nRespuesta:\n- `status`: ok\n- `storage.type`: memory | redis\n- `storage.status`: healthy | unhealthy"
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Body tiene status ok', () => {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.status).to.eql('ok');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Body tiene storage info', () => {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.expect(json.storage).to.have.property('type');",
                  "  pm.expect(json.storage).to.have.property('status');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Responde en menos de 200ms', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(200);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Prometheus Metrics",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/metrics",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["metrics"]
